<para>Shows the dialog, returning one of wxID_OK, wxID_CANCEL, wxID_YES, wxID_NO. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><ref refid="classwx_rich_message_dialog_1a72649d6bd600bbb7c09fb5b0d0d95291" kindref="member">IsCheckBoxChecked()</ref> can be called afterwards to retrieve the value of the check box if one was used. </para>        </detaileddescription>
